I have heard and talk to many Viet Vets. that went back to Vietnam as tourist or doing charity work..etc..  Many of them amazed how friendly and how forgiving the Vietnamese are.  As one Viet Vet. said &quot; They all look at me as a friend not as a formal enemy.  People over there are so welcome us Viet Vet. which is very UNLIKE the attitude of most American toward Vietnamese.&quot;  I just can't recite enough of positive experience that all the Viet Vets. told me.<br><br>
Whenever I encountered such a question such as HOW COME THE VIETNAMESE ARE SO FORGIVING\EASY TO FORGET THE PAST?  My answer is that as a Vietnamese American, I am not so sure that the Vietnamese are more forgiving or easily to forget the past.  My only explaination to such behavior\act is that WE VIETNAMESE LEARNED BY CONDITION TO FORGET AND FORGIVE OUR FORMER ADVERSARY.  This comes from thousand of years fighting the Chinese domination then hundred of years with the French, then the Japanese, then the cold which divided Vietnam into North and South.<br><br>
If we Vietnamese kept on holding the past then we don't have many friends around the world.  After all, the Chinese, the Japanese, the French and the American are very important to Vietnam's economy as well as international intergration.  Holding the past agaisnt these guys is holding a knife to your kneck
